---
alwaysApply: true
---
- All UI components are organized by functional category in `resources/views/components/ui/`:
  - `inputs/`: button, input, textarea, select, checkbox, radio, range, toggle, file-input, color-picker
  - `navigation/`: breadcrumbs, menu, pagination, navbar, sidebar, tabs, steps, stepper
  - `layout/`: card, hero, footer, divider, list, list-row, stack, crud-layout, crud-section, grid-layout
  - `data-display/`: badge, avatar, kbd, table, stat, progress, radial-progress, status, timeline, file-preview
  - `overlay/`: modal, drawer, dropdown, popover, popconfirm, tooltip
  - `media/`: carousel, lightbox, media-gallery, embed, leaflet, hover-gallery
  - `feedback/`: alert, toast, loading, skeleton, callout, empty-state
  - `communication/`: chat-*, notification-*, conversation-view, inbox, message-list
  - `utilities/`: mockup-*, indicator, dock, fab, clipboard, copy-button
  - `advanced/`: calendar-*, chart, code-editor, filter, onboarding, scroll-*, transfer, tree-view, validator, login-button, wysiwyg, accordion, collapse, countdown, diff, fieldset, join, label, link, mask, rating, swap, theme-controller, hover-3d, text-rotate
  - `partials/`: reusable UI fragments

- Components follow Atomic Design principles (see `atomic-design.mdc`).
- Use the `daisy::` Blade namespace for all components.
- Layouts and templates should only use `ui/*` components—no duplication is allowed. Extract a new component if code is reused.
- Place components by functional purpose, not Atomic Design level.

**Template structure**
- Reusable/stable templates: `resources/views/templates/{category}/{name}.blade.php`
- Templates are exposed as Blade components through the package anonymous component namespace, resolving `x-daisy::templates.*` to `daisy::templates.*`.
- No documentation-only or example-only templates belong in this repository
- See `atomic-design.mdc` for additional template rules.

### Template placement and usage

- All templates are in `resources/views/templates/{category}/{name}.blade.php`.
- Templates are package assets meant to be consumed from a host application.
- Do not mirror templates under `resources/views/components/templates`; `resources/views/templates` is the single source for both `daisy::templates.*` views and `x-daisy::templates.*` component aliases.
